textile_editor
==============

Simple textarea enhancement which adds several buttons applying textile syntax to the selected text.
All in one javascript file inclusion.

Requires jQuery version 1.4+



Installation
============

The following line must be placed after the jquery inclusion. The 'defer' attribute is not required.

<%= javascript_include_tag 'textile_editor', :defer => 'defer' %>



Usage
=====

Add class "textile_editor" to any textarea that you would like to have the textile editor enabled on.


Given the following markup:

  <p>
    <label>Description:</label>

    <textarea class="textile_editor"></textarea>
  </p>


Enabling the textile editor will produce the following markup:

  <p>
    <label>Description:</label>

    <span class="textile_editor_buttons">
      <input type="button" value="b" class="bold">
      <input type="button" value="i" class="italic">
      <input type="button" value="link" class="link">
      <input type="button" value="h1" class="header">
      <input type="button" value="h2" class="header">
      <input type="button" value="h3" class="header">
      <input type="button" value="”" class="bq">
      <input type="button" value="del" class="del">
      <input type="button" value="ins" class="ins">
    </span>

    <textarea class="textile_editor"></textarea>
  </p>



Available keyboard shortcuts:

  CTRL + B - bolded text
  CTRL + I - italic text
  CTRL + U - underlined text
  CTRL + D - stroked text
  CTRL + L - instert link


